        "timestamp": "2017-07-24 17:27:47.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nFor 1.0.0, the way the RESTful API is single-threaded. So there wasn't an easy way to to inject the A&AI result during JUnit testing. Thus, the 2 separate .drl, one for testing and the actual release. I will open a JIRA to change A&AI to use a thread. And then another JIRA for the Junit test to consolidate into one .drl. NOTE: We will also need the same functionality for any RESTful API.",
